# lib/ Code Quality Audit

## Critical Issues

### 1. Unsafe `Obj.set_field` in VM (vm.ml:1152-1183)
The `UPDATE_REC` instruction mutates immutable OCaml list cons cells in-place using
`Obj.repr`/`Obj.set_field`. This breaks OCaml's GC write barrier and relies on internal
heap layout assumptions. A GC update or compiler flag change could silently corrupt memory.

### 2. ~~`find_and_remove` correctness bug (vm.ml:969-977)~~ [FIXED]
Rewrote `find_and_remove` as a pure function with an accumulator parameter. Returns
`(entry, remaining_list)` with a single `vm.return_stack <- remaining` mutation at the
call site, instead of mutating `vm.return_stack` at every recursion level.

### 3. JSON deserializer accepts malformed input (deserialize.ml)
- `true`/`false`/`null` parsed by fixed offset, not content â€” `"taco"` would parse as `true`
- Unterminated strings silently accepted
- Unknown characters silently skipped
- Accessor functions (`json_string`, `json_int`, etc.) return silent defaults (`""`, `0`,
  `false`) on type mismatch instead of errors â€” malformed bytecode becomes wrong-but-silent
  behavior


