## Robustness Gaps

### 14. `failwith` and `assert false` instead of proper errors
- typechecker.ml:4390: `failwith "empty DTypeAnd"` â€” crashes with no source location
- vm.ml, typechecker.ml: ~10 `assert false` arms that would produce `Assert_failure` with
  no diagnostics if hit
- vm.ml:1202: `with _ -> 0` silently swallows all exceptions in `lookup_line`
- vm.ml:188-190: `values_compare` returns `0` (equal) for mismatched types instead of
  raising

### 15. ~~`handler_body_has_resume` incomplete coverage (typechecker.ml)~~ [FIXED]
Unified `handler_body_has_resume` and `handler_body_has_perform` into a shared
`handler_body_walk ~pred` that covers all 40 TEExpr variants (except TEFun â€” closures are
opaque to handler classification). Both functions were missing TEArray, TEConstruct, TEIndex,
TERecordUpdate, TEField, TEFieldAssign, TEWhile, etc. â€” resume in those positions caused
incorrect THOpTry classification. `handler_body_has_resume` additionally missed TEApp,
TEBinop, TEUnop, TECons, TETuple, TERecord, TEIf conditions, and TEMatch scrutinees/guards.

### 16. No parse error recovery
Any single parse error aborts the entire parse. No synchronization at declaration
boundaries. Users get only one error per compilation attempt.

### 17. ~~Effect row variable names silently discarded (typechecker.ml:436-439)~~ [FIXED]
Named effect row variables (e.g., `'e`) now share across the same annotation scope via
an `eff_tvars` hashtable, consistent with how type variables (`'a`) share via `tvars`.
Writing `'e` in two places on the same signature now unifies them to the same effect
row variable.

### 18. `ESeq` doesn't enforce `unit` on discarded arm (typechecker.ml:2001-2004)
`42; "hello"` is silently accepted â€” no warning for discarded non-unit values.


