## Lexer/Parser Specific

### 26. ~~String escape handling duplicated 3 times (lexer.ml)~~ [FIXED]
Extracted `escape_char` helper mapping common escapes (`\n`, `\t`, `\\`, `"`) to
replacement chars. `read_string` and `read_interp_string` both delegate to it.
Interp version handles `{`/`}` first, then falls through. Rune escapes (codepoints) and
nested interpolation (source preservation) left as-is â€” fundamentally different operations.

### 27. ~~`fresh_param_counter` is never-reset global state (parser.ml)~~ [FIXED]
Counter reset to 0 at the start of `parse_program` and `parse_expr_string`, making
generated names (`__p1`, `__p2`) deterministic across invocations.

### 28. ~~`parse_type_decl` duplicates its variant-parsing body for `and` clauses~~ [FIXED]
Extracted `parse_variant_ctors` (23-line variant constructor loop) and `parse_type_rhs`
(dispatches record/variant/alias). Both main type decl and `and` clause call
`parse_type_rhs`, eliminating the duplication.

### 29. `parse_let_decl` is 100 lines mixing 6 responsibilities (parser.ml)
Handles destructuring let, mutable let, recursive let, recursive let with `and`, let-in
detection, and top-level let. Each should be a separate function.

### 30. ~~Error messages use internal token names (parser.ml)~~ [FIXED]
Added `describe_token_kind` to token.ml producing user-friendly names: `AMPAMP` â†’ `"'&&'"`,
`LBRACE` â†’ `"'{'"`, `INT _` â†’ `"integer literal"`, `EOF` â†’ `"end of input"`, etc.
`expect` in parser.ml updated to use it. `pp_token_kind` retained for debugging.

### 31. ~~`lookahead_in_after_balanced` is unbounded O(n) scan (parser.ml)~~ [FIXED]
Added `max_scan = 100` token limit. If exceeded, returns `false` â€” falls through to other
`for` forms which parse correctly or produce a sensible error. 100 tokens is generous for
any real destructuring pattern.

### 32. ~~`resolve_fun_params` desugaring logic implemented 3 times~~ [FIXED]
Added `~is_generated` parameter to `resolve_fun_params`. Lambda site uses
`~is_generated:false`, all other sites use `~is_generated:true`. `wrap_params_expr` and
instance method parsing now delegate to the shared function instead of reimplementing.

### 33. ~~`_constraints` silently discarded in `parse_instance_decl`~~ [FIXED]
Now errors if method-level constraints are non-empty: "constraints on individual instance
methods are not supported". Method-level constraints don't make semantic sense â€” constraints
belong at the instance level.

### 34. ~~`_is_open` silently discarded in type declarations~~ [FIXED]
Now errors if `..` appears in a record type definition: "open record types (..) are not
supported in type definitions". Row polymorphism (`..`) is an annotation-time structural
concept, not valid in nominal type definitions.


## Serialization Specific

### 35. Float formatting logic duplicated (serialize.ml:126-129 and js_codegen.ml:445-447)
Trailing-dot stripping from `%.17g` output appears in both files.

### 36. Opcode number 71 skipped (serialize_bin.ml)
Sequence goes 70, 72 with no comment about the gap. Should document the removed opcode.

### 37. Binary deserializer has no bounds checking (deserialize_bin.ml:14-24)
All reads do unchecked string indexing. Truncated input throws raw `Invalid_argument` with
no context about what was being read.

### 38. Capture kind validation accepts any non-zero as CaptureUpvalue (deserialize_bin.ml:59-60)
Should validate `kind = 0 | 1` explicitly and error on anything else.


